uilding.\n\nCyclical behavior with a dominant period of approximately 49 years emerges throughout the simulation, indicating oscillatory adjustments in management strategies as farmers repeatedly adapt to vegetation recovery cycles and inter-annual rainfall fluctuations. Notable transitions occur at inflection points near years 3 and 46, where the curvature of the trend shifts, reflecting complex interactions between individual risk dispositions, observed pasture conditions, and neighbor behaviors across the landscape." 						 					 				 			 		 		 			 		 		 		





